Question 26. 








MSQ (2M)
Question ID : 8232513142
Consider the following multi-threaded code segment (in a mix of C and pseudo-code), invoked by 
two processes P1 and P2, and each of the processes spawns two threads T1 and T2:
int x = 0; 
 // global 
Lock L1;  
// global 
main() {
create a thread to execute foo();  
// Thread T1 
create a thread to execute foo();  
// Thread T2 
wait for the two threads to finish execution; 
print (x);}
foo() {
int y = 0; 
Acquire L1; 
x = x + 1; 
y - y + 1; 
Release L1; 
print (y);}
Which of the following statement(s) is/are correct?
(A) At least one of P1 and P2 will print the value of x as 4.
(B) Both P1 and P2 will print the value of x as 2.
(C) At least one of the threads will print the value of y as 2.
(D) Both T1 and T2, in both the processes, will print the value of y as 1.
